<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="MuTA52">
<l>eytāṉ marāmara mēḻu mirāmaṉā</l>
<l>yeytāṉam māṉmaṟiyai yēntiḻaikkā – yeytatuvun</l>
<l>teṉṉilaṅkaik kōṉvīḻac ceṉṟu kuṟaḷuruvāy</l>
<l>muṉṉilaṅkaik koṇṭāṉ muyaṉṟu</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>He discharged [arrows] at all seven Cadamba trees as Rāma.</l>
<l>He discharged [arrows] at that fawn for [her with] eminent jewels<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">For the motif of the golden deer followed by Rāma, cf. note on Pū. 15.2.</note>. When,</l>
<l>as soon as he had discharged [arrows at him], the king of Southern Laṅkā fell,</l> 
<l>he once went in the form of a dwarf [and], toiling, took over the earth.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
